# Eval case: emergency-fund-planner

IDEA="Build a local emergency-fund planner for one household. Ingest a bank CSV to estimate average monthly essential expenses via a deterministic categorizer, compute a target emergency corpus (configurable months of runway), compare against current liquid balances, and produce a funding plan. A local LLM narrates the plan and prioritization from structured figures only. Output a Markdown emergency-fund plan."

CONTEXT="Target: single household, laptop-only, no cloud sync. Stack: Python CLI; Pandas; SQLite (encrypted); Ollama 7B optional. Formats: 1 CSV template (bank statement); manual entry for liquid balances. Limits: runway 3 to 12 months; 1 household profile. Non-goals: investment recommendations; insurance advice; cloud LLM default; React UI; multi-user; tax filing; PDF/charts; sending data to cloud. Defer: goal linking; auto-sweep to liquid funds; mobile app."
